easured twice, -twins ANOVA is used when * Categorical explanatory variable with more than two categories. * Comparing more than two population means based on independent samples","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"hSta7sAhAr"}],"key":"kpKO2LjkmH"}],"key":"mJatfacM6e"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"jLPXID09Xk"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The following summary discusses each of the above named sub-cases of C→Q within the context of the hypothesis testing process.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"uCy4CKWTiS"}],"key":"EC5fJhpkTo"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I. Stating the null and alternative hypotheses (H","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"VKGZs4wavh"}],"key":"T447DLrDgv"},{"type":"text","value":"*~0~","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"Rum5cMYnQ8"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"and H","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"ydYscx2YI8"}],"key":"QZMdz8pcyV"},{"type":"text","value":"~a~**).*","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"zzAfHTtJbl"}],"key":"vEQisg7SyB"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/textbook/build/c-q_table2-8670626d22664c941c5a529c4b22ebb1.png","alt":"In a Two-Sample t-test, the hypotheses are: H_0: μ_1 - μ_2 = 0 (or H_0: μ_1 = μ_2), and one of: * H_a: μ_1 - μ_2 < 0 (same as H_a: μ_1 < μ_2) * H_a: μ_1 - μ_2 > 0 (same as H_a: μ_1 > μ_2) * H_a: μ_1 - μ_2 ≠ 0 (same as H_a: μ_1 ≠ μ_2) For a paired t-test, the hypotheses are H_0: μ_d = 0, and one of: * H_a: μ_d < 0, * H_a: μ_d > 0, * H_0: μ_0 ≠ 0. For ANOVA, H_0: μ_0 = μ_2 = ... = μ_k, and H_a:not all μ's are equal","key":"Q16A9oRU6v","urlSource":"images/c-q_table2.png"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In a Two-Sample t-test, the hypotheses are: H_0: μ_1 - μ_2 = 0 (or H_0: μ_1 = μ_2), and one of: * H_a: μ_1 - μ_2 < 0 (same as H_a: μ_1 < μ_2) * H_a: μ_1 - μ_2 > 0 (same as H_a: μ_1 > μ_2) * H_a: μ_1 - μ_2 ≠ 0 (same as H_a: μ_1 ≠ μ_2) For a paired t-test, the hypotheses are H_0: μ_d = 0, and one of: * H_a: μ_d < 0, * H_a: μ_d > 0, * H_0: μ_0 ≠ 0. For ANOVA, H_0: μ_0 = μ_2 = ... = μ_k, and H_a:not all μ’s are equal","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"DWGVo6JfmV"}],"key":"MzQxVYMp8y"}],"key":"TWyGBvuXbC"}],"enumerator":"2","key":"ZApKudHgG7"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"II. Check Conditions, and Summarize the Data Using a Test Statistic","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"key":"BfxRBHgYn0"}],"key":"r1rph7FOyv"}],"key":"uaivNZjRAs"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"*","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"wg5QZos32i"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Check that the conditions under which the test can be reliably used are met.","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"CDRnFmd4x2"}],"key":"ZKzJbuI5fP"}],"key":"Miv